# ── Gotchas & decisions ────────────────────────────────────
@gotcha|issue:tRPC bundle size|detail:Importing the full router on the client pulls all zod schemas into the JS bundle; adds ~45 KB gzipped|fix:Use tRPC lazy router splitting; only import procedure types client-side
@gotcha|issue:PlanetScale connection limits|detail:Serverless functions open a new DB connection per invocation; hits 1000 connection limit under load|fix:Use Prisma Data Proxy or PlanetScale serverless driver (@planetscale/database) with HTTP-based connections
@gotcha|issue:Stale cart in Redis|detail:Redis cart TTL is 7 days; if user returns after expiry, checkout crashes with empty cart and no error message|fix:Cart middleware checks existence before mutations; show recovery UI that re-adds items from order history
@gotcha|issue:Webhook replay storms|detail:Stripe retries failed webhooks exponentially; if handler is down for 2 h, replay storm can cause duplicate order processing|fix:Idempotency key check on order creation; dedup table in PlanetScale with 24 h TTL

@decision|id:ADR-040|title:Next.js App Router over Pages Router|status:accepted|reason:React Server Components reduce client JS by 40%; streaming SSR improves TTFB
@decision|id:ADR-041|title:tRPC over REST|status:accepted|reason:End-to-end type safety eliminates a class of integration bugs; inference removes need for codegen
@decision|id:ADR-042|title:Inngest over BullMQ|status:accepted|reason:Serverless-native; no Redis queue to manage; built-in retry, throttle, and step functions
@decision|id:ADR-043|title:PlanetScale over Supabase|status:accepted|reason:Non-blocking schema migrations (no table locks); better branching workflow for CI

@component|name:Next.js App|file:apps/web/|does:SSR storefront, API routes, tRPC server, edge middleware
@component|name:Prisma Schema|file:packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma|does:Canonical data model — products, orders, users, inventory
@component|name:tRPC Router|file:packages/api/src/router/|does:Type-safe API layer; procedures grouped by domain (catalog, cart, order)
@component|name:Inngest Functions|file:packages/jobs/src/functions/|does:Async workflows — order confirmation, shipment tracking, inventory reconciliation

@config|param:NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_KEY|value:pk_live_***|note:Publishable key; safe for client bundle
@config|param:RATE_LIMIT_MAX|value:100|note:100 requests per 10s window per IP
@config|param:CART_TTL_SECONDS|value:604800|note:7-day cart expiry in Redis
@config|param:IMAGE_QUALITY|value:75|note:Vercel image optimization quality; balances size vs. fidelity

@entry|use-case:Browse and purchase|command:Browser -> Vercel -> SSR catalog page -> Add to cart (Redis) -> Checkout (tRPC) -> Stripe -> Order confirmation (Inngest -> Resend)
@entry|use-case:Admin product upload|command:Admin UI -> tRPC mutation -> Prisma write -> S3 image upload -> Algolia index sync

@note|context:performance|text:Lighthouse score 95+ on catalog pages; checkout flow is client-side SPA after initial SSR to avoid navigation latency
@note|context:cost|text:Vercel Pro ($20/mo) + PlanetScale Scaler ($29/mo) + Upstash Pay-as-you-go; total ~$80/mo at 10K orders/mo
